{"CVE_ID": "CVE-2023-6738", "Description": "The Page Builder: Pagelayer \u2013 Drag and Drop website builder plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Stored Cross-Site Scripting via the 'pagelayer_header_code', 'pagelayer_body_open_code', and 'pagelayer_footer_code' meta fields in all versions up to, and including, 1.7.8 due to insufficient input sanitization and output escaping on user supplied attributes. This makes it possible for authenticated attackers with contributor-level and above permissions to inject arbitrary web scripts in pages that will execute whenever a user accesses an injected page. This appears to be a reintroduction of a vulnerability patched in version 1.7.7.", "CWE Name": "CWE-79", "CWE Description": "The software does not neutralize or incorrectly neutralizes user-controllable input before it is placed in output that is used as a web page that is served to other users.", "Associated MITRE ATT&CK Technique": "T1189", "Severity": "MEDIUM", "Known Vulnerable Software": "[\"{'operator': 'OR', 'negate': False, 'cpeMatch': [{'vulnerable': True, 'criteria': 'cpe:2.3:a:pagelayer:pagelayer:*:*:*:*:*:wordpress:*:*', 'versionEndIncluding': '1.7.8', 'matchCriteriaId': '4E8DCB12-9FB0-4B9A-A245-C7E897C76906'}]}\"]", "Mitigation Techniques": "M1050, M1051, M1048, M1021, M1017"}
